{"questionId":"9084633","questionHtml":"<p>What is the escape speed from the surface of a planet of radius <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math></em> that has an acceleration of gravity <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> </em>at its surface?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi></msqrt></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084633","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.HL.TZ0.26","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"What is the escape speed from the surface of a planet of radius r that has an acceleration of gravity g at its surface? A. gr B. gr C. 2gr D. 2gr","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"26","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D. Fields","D.1 Gravitational fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}